Location: WebSocket server shutdown handling

Current State:
- No explicit cleanup of serial connections on Ctrl+C  
- asyncio.Future() used but no proper task cancellation handlers  
- Serial port resources may remain open after program termination  
- No signal handlers for SIGTERM/SIGINT before exit

Suggested Improvements:
1. Add signal handlers to close all connections and reset hardware state  
2. Implement proper async context managers or cleanup hooks  
3. Track active tasks and cancel them gracefully on shutdown  
4. Add final health check before reporting "Server stopped"
5. Document expected shutdown sequence in README